"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.1.1\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.1.1</span> 標題：軛（yoke）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： מוֹט, מוֹטָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： mot, motah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:13\">LEV 26:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:6\">ISA 58:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:6\">ISA 58:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:9\">ISA 58:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:2\">JER 27:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:10\">JER 28:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:12\">JER 28:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:13\">JER 28:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:13\">JER 28:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek30:18\">EZK 30:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:27\">EZK 34:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:13\">NAM 1:13</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： עֹל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： ‘ol)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:40\">GEN 27:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:13\">LEV 26:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:2\">NUM 19:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:3\">DEU 21:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:48\">DEU 28:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:7\">1SA 6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:4\">1KI 12:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:4\">1KI 12:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:11\">1KI 12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:11\">1KI 12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:14\">1KI 12:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:14\">1KI 12:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:4\">2CH 10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:4\">2CH 10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:11\">2CH 10:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:11\">2CH 10:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:14\">2CH 10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:3\">ISA 9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:27\">ISA 10:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:27\">ISA 10:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:25\">ISA 14:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:6\">ISA 47:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:20\">JER 2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:5\">JER 5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:8\">JER 27:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:11\">JER 27:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:12\">JER 27:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:2\">JER 28:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:4\">JER 28:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:11\">JER 28:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:14\">JER 28:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:8\">JER 30:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:14\">LAM 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:27\">LAM 3:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:27\">EZK 34:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:4\">HOS 11:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： βοοζύγιον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： boozugion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir26:7\">SIR 26:7</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： ἑτεροζυγέω</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： heterozugeō)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:14\">2CO 6:14</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： κλοιός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： kloios)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir6:24\">SIR 6:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir6:29\">SIR 6:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir21:25\">SIR 21:25</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： ζυγός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： zugos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:29\">MAT 11:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:30\">MAT 11:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:10\">ACT 15:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:1\">GAL 5:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:1\">1TI 6:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir28:19\">SIR 28:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir28:20\">SIR 28:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir28:20\">SIR 28:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir28:25\">SIR 28:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir33:27\">SIR 33:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir40:1\">SIR 40:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir42:4\">SIR 42:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir51:26\">SIR 51:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc8:18\">1MA 8:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc8:31\">1MA 8:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc13:41\">1MA 13:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3Macc4:9\">3MA 4:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/PssSol7:9\">PSS 7:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/PssSol17:30\">PSS 17:30</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>軛是一根木杆或一個木架子，通常架在兩頭役畜的脖子上，將其連在一起，這樣牲畜就可以更有效率地一起拉犁、拉脫粒板、拉耙或拉車。另外也有人背的軛，但通常是給一個人使用的索具。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0316_slaves_in_yokes.jpg\" alt=\"被枷鎖的奴隸\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">被枷鎖的奴隸 (© Osama Shukir Muhammed Amin FRCP(Glasg), CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>軛通過項圈固定在牲畜的脖子上，項圈是由木頭、藤條或繩子製成。軛的中間用繩索或杆子連接到需要牽拉的物件上，這樣兩頭牲畜就能並排一起牽拉。有時，人們也會把軛放在俘虜（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:10\">JER 28:10</a> ）或奴隸的身上，以限制他們移動或防止他們逃跑。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>如果當地文化不知道或不熟悉役畜負軛，翻譯者可以將<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:2\">NUM 19:2</a> （以及<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:3\">DEU 21:3</a> ）中原文字面意為「未曾負過軛的」一語譯為：「未曾乾過活的」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 直譯）。</p>\n<p>在所有新約經文和部分舊約經文中，「軛」用作比喻，象徵奴僕的服從和被奴役的狀態。在這種情況下（如：<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:13\">LEV 26:13</a> ；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:27\">ISA 10:27</a> ；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:2\">JER 28:2</a> ，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:14\">JER 28:14</a> ，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:8\">JER 30:8</a> ；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:27\">EZK 34:27</a> ；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:13\">NAM 1:13</a> ；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:10\">ACT 15:10</a> ；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:1\">GAL 5:1</a> ；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:1\">1TI 6:1</a> ），翻譯者可以不按照字面意思來翻譯，而是將其喻意表達出來（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:13\">LEV 26:13</a> 「……我打碎了壓制你們的權勢……」；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 直譯）。同樣，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir40:1\">SIR 40:1</a> 可以譯成「……沉重的擔子壓在我們所有人身上……」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 直譯）。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:5\">LAM 5:5</a> 中可能提到了「軛」，參《〈耶利米哀歌〉手冊》（<em>A Handbook on Lamentations</em> ）第134頁中的註解。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir33:27\">SIR 33:27</a> 中，負軛意指戴著特製的「索具」或「項圈」。這是一種套在脖子上的繩子、皮條、藤條或木製物品，軛就連接在這個物品上面。在這節經文中，它與控制牲畜的動作有關，因此<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Italian Common Language Version\">ITCL</abbr> 將這個詞譯為「韁繩」。在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir6:24\">SIR 6:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir6:29\">SIR 6:29</a> 中，<em>kloios</em> 是一個象徵。在許多語言中，可以保留鎖鏈和軛等詞語。然而，如果某種語言不允許這樣使用，那麼可以譯成「讓你的所有行為都受智慧管治」（6:24），以及「如果你讓智慧管治你，你就會保有平安，你就能掌管發生在你身上的事」（6:29）。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
